      • computeStepSize

        public int computeStepSize()
        Compute the step size. Since the attenuator is an integer we must round to the nearest whole number. This means not all steps will be the same size if the goal is to include the min value and the max value exactly. In particular the current algorithm assumes the last step is of varying size.
        Returns:
        The step size (for all but last step, which vary to reach max attenuator exactly)
